.AVIATION...
(12Z TAFS)
Issued at 417 AM PDT Tue Mar 17 2026

Fairly straight forward TAFs today as strong high pressure and
clear skies dominate the pattern. Winds will be diurnally driven
with light offshore winds in the morning and moderate onshore
winds in the afternoon. There is some indication in the guidance
for low ceilings and fog to roll in Wednesday morning, but the air
mass seems too dry to support that. We`ll see if the trend holds
through the day.

Vicinity of SFO...NW winds should soon shift to a light NE breeze
before flipping back to a moderate NW breeze in the afternoon.
Otherwise clear skies will dominate today.

SFO Bridge Approach...Similar to SFO.

Monterey Bay Terminals...VFR conditions through the TAF period
with diurnally driven wind direction. Again there is some
indication that a shallow marine layer will sneak in low ceilings
and fog Wednesday morning, but I need to see more evidence that it
will be different than the clear skies this morning before
including anything in the TAFS.

